text: @Apurvasrani And like you said, how many people can really afford that. If this comes at a cost that most people can‚Äôt afford, we have to look at alternative solutions because it‚Äôs just not worth it to be miserable all the tile.

name: Ishita Yadav
text: @Apurvasrani Of course. Again, like I said, whatever works for you. I have (had) a friend who feels that therapy really helps her but then again she pays 3500 per session and she has 4 sessions in a month and I could SEE a change in her, like the way she responded to situations.

name: Ishita Yadav
text: @Apurvasrani And I feel like urban India is getting there. It feels like the easiest solution but you have to dig deeper and try harder and it‚Äôs not always as simple as it seems.  Ok rant over. üôà

name: Ishita Yadav
text: @Apurvasrani I saw this show when I was 23, Six Feet Under, and I don‚Äôt remember a lot of it other than the finale, but I do remember this one line that stuck with me - Therapy is for Americans what vodka is for Russians. Habit-forming and destroys your ability to lead a normal life.

name: Ishita Yadav
text: @Apurvasrani And if you‚Äôre not looking for someone objective (although, I must add that most Indian therapists are CRAZY judgemental) to just direct you to a solution and you just feel like you need someone to vent to, there are always (global) therapy apps that aren‚Äôt as expensive.

name: Ishita Yadav
text: @Apurvasrani And I‚Äôm not trying to be condescending or even to diminish someone‚Äôs struggles, but at the end of the day, we are the only ones who are responsible for how we feel. The world will bring us down every single day if we let it.

name: Ishita Yadav
text: @Apurvasrani of why you are the way you are, why you feel the way that you do, and the tools to overcome that. And it‚Äôs all available for free. If anyone REALLY wants to help themselves, there is always a way out, even if they don‚Äôt have the dough to get talk therapy.

name: Ishita Yadav
text: @Apurvasrani Also, since the point of talk therapy is to become more self aware through the eyes of another, if you can‚Äôt afford it or if you don‚Äôt trust a stranger with your problems, there are several alternatives like books and YouTube videos that can help you become more self aware (cont)

name: Ishita Yadav
text: @Apurvasrani There are several. Meditation, exercise and a healthy diet are scientifically proven to make you feel better. I know people hate it when I say that but losing my brother was extremely traumatic and all these things greatly helped me just get on with each day.

name: Ishita Yadav
text: @Apurvasrani Also, therapy doesn‚Äôt work for everyone. Opening up to a stranger about their lives can make some people MORE anxious. Addressing some issues can break some people down more. People need to stop talking about therapy as the ONLY answer. It may work for some, it doesn‚Äôt for all.
